title: fanoutqa: Which Formula 1 Grand Prix races have been hosted in Asia/Middle East and which driver has the most wins on each of these tracks? (697563de476221c4)

chat_history.content: Which Formula 1 Grand Prix races have been hosted in Asia/Middle East and which driver has the most wins on each of these tracks?

Here is a list of Formula One Grand Prix races that have been hosted in Asia and the Middle East, alongside the drivers with the most wins on each track:

- **Bahrain International Circuit**: This race has been won the most by Sebastian Vettel with 5 wins.
- **Marina Bay Street Circuit**: Sebastian Vettel has also won this Grand Prix the most, with 5 wins as well.
- **Shanghai International Circuit**: Lewis Hamilton has won this race 5 times.
- **Sepang International Circuit**: Michael Schumacher won this race 3 times.
- **Suzuka Circuit**: Michael Schumacher has 6 wins at this track.
- **Fuji Speedway**: James Hunt and Mario Andretti have both won this race once.
- **Indian Grand Prix**: Sebastian Vettel won this race two years in a row.
- **Korean International Circuit**: Sebastian Vettel has won all three races held at this track.
- **Baku City Circuit**: This race has been won the most by Lewis Hamilton.
- **Yas Marina Circuit**: Lewis Hamilton has raced to victory 5 times at this track.
- **Buddh International Circuit**: Vettel won the race in 2012 and 2013.
- **Hanoi Street Circuit**: This race has not yet been raced.
